      "title": "See also"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Broadcasting rules apply, see the "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "https://numpy.org/doc/stable/reference/generated/numpy.linalg.html",
              "href": "",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "linalg",
              "text": "fnp.linalg"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " documentation for\ndetails."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "This is implemented using the "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "_geev"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " LAPACK routines which compute\nthe eigenvalues and eigenvectors of general square arrays."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Illustration, using the fact that the eigenvalues of a diagonal matrix\nare its diagonal elements, that multiplying a matrix on the left\nby an orthogonal matrix, "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "Q"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", and on the right by "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "Q.T"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " (the transpose\nof "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "Q"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "), preserves the eigenvalues of the \"middle\" matrix. In other words,\nif "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "Q"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is orthogonal, then "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "Q * A * Q.T"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " has the same eigenvalues as\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "A"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ":"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import flopscope as fnp"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "from numpy import linalg as LA"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "x = fnp.random.random()"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "Q = fnp.array([[fnp.cos(x), -fnp.sin(x)], [fnp.sin(x), fnp.cos(x)]])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "LA.norm(Q[0, :]), LA.norm(Q[1, :]), fnp.dot(Q[0, :],Q[1, :])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "(1.0, 1.0, 0.0)"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Now multiply a diagonal matrix by "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "Q"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " on one side and\nby "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "Q.T"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " on the other:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "D = fnp.diag((-1,1))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "LA.eigvals(D)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([-1.,  1.])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "A = fnp.dot(Q, D)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "A = fnp.dot(A, Q.T)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "LA.eigvals(A)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([ 1., -1.]) # random"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Examples"
    }
  ],
